comments: Jackson (IND) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Barrett (TOR), which affects his layup attempt.
Poeltl (TOR) rests a hand on Jackson's (IND) body and the contact during his shot attempt in the post is marginal.
Jackson (IND) legally contests Poeltl's (TOR) layup attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Barnes (TOR) loses possession of the ball and his momentum carries him forwards into Haliburton (IND).  The contact during the loose ball is incidental.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Trent Jr. (TOR) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Barrett (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Haliburton's (IND) possession.
The ball goes off of Haliburton's (IND) leg and out of bounds and Toronto is given possession.
Jackson (IND) turns to roll and marginal contact occurs with Barnes (TOR) as Jackson releases away from the contact during the pick.

Barnes (TOR) blocks the dunk attempt by Jackson (IND) before following through and making some contact with his head.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Nembhard (IND) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Barnes's (TOR) left arm.
Jackson (IND) jumps vertically and legally contests the driving shot attempt by Barnes (TOR).
Barrett (TOR) moves alongside Siakam's (IND) path and marginal body contact occurs while defending his driving shot attempt.
Sheppard (IND) jumps into Poeltl (TOR) and reaches across his right arm, initiating illegal contact that prevents Poeltl from gathering the loose ball.

Barnes (TOR) briefly has an arm wrapped around Nembhard (IND), who places a bent forearm against Barnes's body.  The contact from Nembhard is marginal and does not dislodge Barnes from his defensive position.
Poeltl (TOR) commits a take foul on Jackson (IND).
Barrett (TOR) does not release the throw-in within five seconds.
Barrett (TOR) places his forearm to Sheppard's (IND) front and marginal body contact occurs as Barrett releases away from the contact at the end of his drive.
Sheppard (IND) maintains a legal guarding position during Barrett's (TOR) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
